[[Glen Canyon National Recreational Area|Glen Canyon NRA Map]] is in spans across south central Utah from lower Cataract Canyon and the board of Canyonlands National Park in the northeast, to Page, Marble Canyon, and Vermilion Cliffs National Monument on the southwest. The northern boundary of the recreational area spans from the Henry Mountains past Capitol Reef National Park to Grand Staircase-Escalante National Monument, and the southern end borders the Navajo Nation.

